THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES,
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community,
Having regard to Council Directive 77/93/EEC of 21 December 1976 on protective measures against the introduction into the Member States of organisms harmful to plants or plant products (1), as last amended by Commission Directive 91/27/EEC (2), and in particular Annex III, part B (10) thereof,
Whereas under the provisions of Directive 77/93/EEC from 16 April to 31 October, in the case of origin in the Northern Hemisphere, and from 1 November to 15 April, in the case of origin in the Southern Hemisphere, plants of certain genera, other than fruit and seeds, originating in countries or regions other than those recognized as being free from Erwinia amylovora (Burr.) Winsl. et al., may not be introduced in certain Member States;
